    A Google Compute Engine snapshot. Compute Engine allows you to take snapshots of your persistent disk and create new persistent disks from that snapshot. This can be useful for backing up data, recreating a persistent disk that might have been lost, or copying a persistent disk. Snapshots can be applied across persistent disk types.
